SIMPLE: adhesive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adhesive
<hw>Ad*he"sive</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>adh⟦eacute⟧sif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sticky; tenacious, as
glutinous substances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Apt or tending to adhere; clinging.</def>
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Adhesive attraction</b></col>. <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<cd>See <er>Attraction</er></cd>. -- <col><b>Adhesive
inflammation</b></col> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>, <cd>that kind of inflammation
which terminates in the reunion of divided parts without
suppuration.</cd> -- <col><b>Adhesive plaster</b></col>, <cd>a sticking;
a plaster containing resin, wax, litharge, and olive oil.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adhesively</ent>⟦br⟧
